description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to work as an expert and leader in your field in one of the most beautiful coastal areas of the UK?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an exceptional Pharmacist who has significant clinical experience in caring for Older People and strategic leadership skills to drive an integrated approach to improving pharmaceutical care for our frail elderly population across Swansea Bay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Consultant Pharmacist for Older People is an exciting new post for the Health Board. You will lead the integrated Older People’s Pharmacy Group, acting as the driver to achieve a co-ordinated and structured approach to change the pharmacy delivery model for older people. You will work across acute, primary and community care, in close collaboration Pharmacy teams, consultant geriatricians, primary care professionals, GP clusters and mental health teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Swansea Bay University Health Board has strong links with Swansea University. The new School of Pharmacy will provide a key opportunity for the post holder to lead and manage research in pharmaceutical care for frail elderly and act as a role model to inspire colleagues to undertake research in this area by providing support and leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post. English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Judith VincentClinical Director for Pharmacy and Medicines Management&lt;/p&gt;
